{
  "doc_id": "10717",
  "text": "Intussusception is a condition in which a segment of intestine invaginates into another section of intestine. Signs and symptoms of intussusception include acute pain, nausea, lethargy, vomiting and sometimes bleeding from the rectum (\"red currant jelly\") [CITATION_1] . Although intussusception generally remits spontaneously, in a number of cases either contrast enema or surgery is needed to treat the disorder [CITATION_2] . The causes of intussusception include infections and vaccination with rotavirus vaccine, but organic disorders such as malignancy tend to predominate in adults.",
